HEADWORD: Emication
<hw>Em`i*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>emicatio</ets>, fr. <ets>emicare</ets> to spring out or forth;
<ets>e</ets> out + <ets>micare</ets> to move quickly to and fro, to
sparkle.]</ety> <def>A flying off in small particles, as heated iron or
fermenting liquors; a sparkling; scintillation.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

